customrecordtype.description: This record hold the setup for the different types of encryption needs for the organisation.

customrecordcustomfield.description: Select which type of encryption that should be used.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Select which type of encryption that should be used.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Encryption Type

customrecordcustomfield.description: Check this box to indicate that the input file should be encrypted. Otherwise it will try to decrypt the file.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Check this box to indicate that the input file should be encrypted. Otherwise it will try to decrypt the file.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Encrypt

customrecordcustomfield.description: Enter the internal ID of the folder that you want to monitor for new files. Each Crypto Setup record needs its own folder to be able to process them differently. The folder monitoring is optional, leave this blank if you don't want this job setup-record to look for new files in a directory. Other ways of initiating the encryption is through Workflow Actions.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter the internal ID of the folder that you want to monitor for new files. Each Crypto Setup record needs its own folder to be able to process them differently. The folder monitoring is optional, leave this blank if you don't want this job setup-record to look for new files in a directory. Other ways of initiating the encryption is through Workflow Actions.
customrecordcustomfield.label: File Input/Monitor Folder

customrecordcustomfield.description: Set the internal id of a folder for the output file. If this field is empty, the file will remain in the original folder.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Set the internal id of a folder for the output file. If this field is empty, the file will remain in the original folder.
customrecordcustomfield.label: File Output Folder

customrecordcustomfield.description: If this box is checked, a copy of the original file will be created the chosen folder.
customrecordcustomfield.help: If this box is checked, a copy of the original file will be created the chosen folder.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Store a copy of the original file

customrecordcustomfield.description: Enter an internal id for a folder where you want to store the copy of the original file.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter an internal id for a folder where you want to store the copy of the original file.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Folder for copy of original file

customrecordcustomfield.description: Enter an internal id for a folder where you want to store the files that fail.
customrecordcustomfield.help: Enter an internal id for a folder where you want to store the files that fail.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Folder for erroneous files

customrecordcustomfield.description: This is the id for the public key used in encrypting files. This is normally supplied by the receiving party.
customrecordcustomfield.help: This is the id for the public key used in encrypting files. This is normally supplied by the receiving party.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Encryption Public Key

customrecordcustomfield.description: This is the passphrase that was used for generating the private decryption key.
customrecordcustomfield.help: This is the passphrase that was used for generating the private decryption key.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Private key passphrase

customrecordcustomfield.description: This is the id for the private key used in decrypting files. This needs to be created using a key generator.
customrecordcustomfield.help: This is the id for the private key used in decrypting files. This needs to be created using a key generator.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Decryption Private Key

customrecordcustomfield.description: This is the id for the public key used in decrypting files. This needs to be generated with a key-generator
customrecordcustomfield.help: This is the id for the public key used in decrypting files. This needs to be generated with a key-generator
customrecordcustomfield.label: Decryption Public Key
